{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/InitiallyUnownedRef\/takeRef()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/initiallyunownedref\/takeref()"]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GLibObject","title":"takeRef()","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject19InitiallyUnownedRefV","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"method"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/InitiallyUnownedRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/InitiallyUnownedRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In other words, this function will convert a floating reference (if","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"present) into a full reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically you want to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this function is helpful."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"GObject. We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"where the object that is being returned already exists).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the same time, the API style of some popular GObject-based"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"libraries (such as Gtk) make it likely that for newly-created GObject"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instances, the user can be saved some typing if they are allowed to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"return a floating reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them. The caller will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that has been converted to a full reference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_object_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" running at the same time in another thread on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object"},{"type":"text","text":" instance. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"text":" runs first then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_take_ref()"},{"text":" runs first then the result will be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"additional reference on top of that one is added. It is best to avoid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this situation."}]}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/InitiallyUnownedRef":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/InitiallyUnownedRef","title":"InitiallyUnownedRef","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/initiallyunownedref","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"InitiallyUnownedRef"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A type for objects that have an initially floating reference.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InitiallyUnownedRef","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","abstract":[],"title":"GLibObject","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"role":"symbol","title":"ObjectRef"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/InitiallyUnownedRef/takeRef()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/InitiallyUnownedRef\/takeRef()","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/initiallyunownedref\/takeref()","role":"symbol","title":"takeRef()","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","text":"ObjectRef"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}]},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/InitiallyUnownedRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/InitiallyUnownedRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/initiallyunownedref\/objectprotocol-implementations","type":"topic","abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object":{"title":"Object","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"role":"symbol"}}}